description:
## Problem
When the Electron app is launched from Finder/Dock, it shows empty because it can't find the correct Node.js (needs v22 from nvm).

The app spawns `claude` at main.js:156, but Finder doesn't inherit the shell PATH that includes nvm's Node.

## Fix
Modify main.js spawn call to explicitly include the nvm Node path in the env, e.g.:
```js
const claude = spawn('claude', ['--print'], {
  env: {
    ...process.env,
    PATH: `/Users/mandrigin/.nvm/versions/node/v22.x.x/bin:${process.env.PATH}`
  },
  ...
});
```

Or detect the nvm path dynamically. The goal is for the app to work when double-clicked from Finder, not just from terminal.
